Realizing Rowena is trying to recruit and train followers in the art of witchcraft, Sam and Dean come up with a plan to catch her before she can do much damage. Meanwhile, Hannah runs into a blast from her vessel's past, which complicates things for her and Castiel.

name: Hibbing 911
summary: Jody Mills reluctantly attends a mandatory sheriff's retreat and is partnered with an overeager sheriff named Donna who wants to bond. Just as Jody thinks things can't get any worse, a body with just strings of meat and skin hanging off the bones is discovered. While the local sheriffs blame an animal attack, Jody knows better and calls Sam and Dean.

name: The Things We Left Behind
summary: Castiel finds Jimmy's daughter Claire in a group home and she convinces him to break her out. After she runs away from him, Castiel calls Sam and Dean to help find her before she gets in trouble. Meanwhile, Crowley faces his biggest challenge yet.

name: The Hunter Games
summary: After the massacre at the ranch, Dean, Sam and Castiel double their efforts to find a cure for the Mark of Cain but there is nothing in the lore that can help them. Desperate, Castiel comes up with an idea that Sam deems the "single worst idea I've ever heard." Meanwhile, Rowena continues to plot against Crowley, and Castiel tries to mend his relationship with Claire who is plotting revenge against Dean for killing her friend.

name: There's No Place Like Home
summary: Sam is scanning the internet for suspicious paranormal activity and comes across a video of Charlie beating up a district attorney. Dean suspects she's back from Oz and hunting on her own, assuming the district attorney must have been a demon. When they do find Charlie, they are shocked when she tells them why she really came back from Oz.

name: About a Boy
summary: Looking to get Dean out of the bunker, Sam finds a case for him and Dean to investigate - people are disappearing into thin air with only their clothes left behind. Sam and Dean suspect fairies or angels, but the truth turns out to be much more shocking - Hansel, from Hansel and Gretel lore, is kidnapping people and turning them into their younger selves to placate the evil witch. Unfortunately, Dean finds this information out the hard way after he becomes Hansel's next victim and reverts to his 14 year old self.

name: Halt & Catch Fire
summary: Ghost starts killing people through various electronic devices. Sam and Dean discover who was killed and why this ghost is seeking revenge on a group of college students but what they can't figure out is how he's doing it. With three dead, the brothers must stop the ghost before he claims his next victim.

name: The Executioner's Song
summary: Dean, Sam and Castiel deal with Cain's return. Crowley and Rowena continue to grow closer but when Crowley bails on plans with his mother to help the Winchesters, Rowena lets him have it.

name: The Things They Carried
summary: Despite Dean's directive to forget about looking for a cure for the Mark of Cain, Sam continues to do research. Dean suspects Sam is hiding something but decides to focus on a new murder case where they run into Cole. The three team up and learn a Khan worm is infecting men and turning them into murderers. Unfortunately, the worm makes it's way into Cole.

name: Paint It Black
summary: Sam and Dean investigate a string of suicides committed by people with little in common other than the identical, grisly method of death - slow, self-administered disembowlment. All of the victims were members of a Catholic church and had recently given confession, leading the brothers to suspect the priest is somehow involved. Meanwhile, when Crowley captures Olivette, the leader of the Grand Coven, Rowena pleads her case to be allowed to practice magic freely again.

name: Inside Man
summary: Sam and Castiel follow up on a lead about the Mark of Cain. Dean and Rowena meet.

name: Book of the Damned
summary: Charlie calls Sam and Dean to tell them she found the Book of the Dead which could help remove the Mark of Cain. The Winchesters race to her after she tells them she's been shot by a man named Jacob Styne who says the book belongs to his family and he won't rest until he gets it back. Castiel and Metatron take a road trip to find Castiel's grace but they hit a couple road bumps along the way.

name: The Werther Project
summary: Sam learns that former Men of Letters, Magnus, once built a magical box and Sam sets out to find it in the hopes it can cure Dean of the Mark of Cain. However, what he's not prepared for is the deadly alarm system Magnus set up on the box. When Sam opens the box, he puts both his and Dean's life in danger.

name: Angel Heart
summary: When Claire Novak gets a lead on her mother, Amelia, who has been missing for years, Castiel asks Sam and Dean to help her. Castiel feels guilty for what he did to the Novak family and wants to make amends by reuniting Claire with her mom. However, when they find out what took Amelia, they realize there is a chance Claire may not get her happy ending.

name: Dark Dynasty
summary: Dean and Sam investigate a bizarre murder and realize the killer bears the same tattoo as those from the Styne family. Eldon Styne attacks Dean and a brutal fight ensues. Meanwhile, Castiel acts as referee when Charlie and Rowena are forced to work together on the Book of the Damned. Crowley discovers his mother is missing and knows she's up to something so he turns to an old enemy for help.

name: The Prisoner
summary: When it comes to the Stynes, Dean decides to take matters into his own hands. Sam tries to come to terms with his decision.

name: Brother's Keeper
summary: Dean makes a shocking decision regarding the Mark of Cain that would change not only his life, but Sam's too. Meanwhile, Crowley and Rowena face off and Castiel gets caught in the middle.

name: Out of the Darkness, Into the Fire
summary: After the Darkness passes over them, Sam and Dean wake up and Dean realizes that he encountered the creature at the heart of the storm. Meanwhile, Castiel prays to Heaven to help him, and Crowley takes steps to avoid Castiel.

name: Form and Void
summary: While Sam tries to find a cure for the Darkness virus invading his body, Dean takes Jenna to her grandmother's. Meanwhile, the angels torture Castiel for Metatron's information, and Crowley learns of the Darkness.

name: The Bad Seed
summary: When the Winchesters learn of demons killing witches, they approach one and have her find them Rowena so that they can have her cure Castiel. Meanwhile, Crowley raises the young Amara in Hell but soon discovers that the Darkness may be beyond his control.

name: Baby
summary: Sam and Dean battle a part-vampire/part-ghoul creature that is trying to raise an army to fight the coming Darkness. Meanwhile, Sam receives another cryptic vision, and the Impala witnesses everything.

name: Thin Lizzie
summary: Sam and Dean track down a double axe-murder at Lizzie Borden's home, and soon realize that something supernatural is involved. As they continue their investigation, they soon discover that Amara is responsible for creating an army of soulless killers.

name: Our Little World
summary: Sam and Dean get a lead on Amara's location, and try to break in to Crowley's stronghold to kill the embodiment of the Darkness. Meanwhile, Castiel tracks down Metatron and finds him in sorry straits.

name: Plush
summary: A college student wearing a rabbit mask kills a man in Minnesota, and Sheriff Donna calls in Sam and Dean for help. They soon deal with the rabbit, but a harlequin and then a clown attack the local high school coach. Meanwhile, Dean finds Sam praying to God.

name: Just My Imagination
summary: Sam's imaginary friend Sully appears at the bunker and asks the Winchesters for help. Someone is murdering his fellow imaginary friends, and he needs hunters to track the killer down.

name: O Brother Where Art Thou?
summary: While Sam enters Hell with Crowley and Rowena to confront Lucifer and seek his help defeating Amara, Dean investigates the scene of Amara's recent killing and discovers that she has plans for him.

name: The Devil in the Details
summary: Lucifer takes Sam on a trip through Sam's memories to convince him to agree to possession. Meanwhile, Castiel goes to determine if Amara is dead, and Dean and Crowley come up with a plan to send Lucifer back to his cage.

name: Into the Mystic
summary: When Sam is unable to sleep and won't leave the bunker, Dean suggests that they look into the case of a retiree who bashed his head in while yelling that he could hear someone screaming.

name: Don't You Forget About Me
summary: Sam and Dean pay a visit to Jody after one of her wards, Claire Novak, calls them and insists that there are monsters in their town. A corpse soon turns up, and Jody and the Winchesters realize that Claire was right.

name: Love Hurts
summary: When a babysitter is murdered on Valentine's Day and her heart torn out of her chest, the Winchesters learn about it and investigate. They discover that an ancient curse is responsible for the death, and that it's passed on by kissing. To save the next victim, Dean kisses her... marking himself for death.

name: The Vessel
summary: The Winchesters launch a desperate attempt to recover an artifact capable of destroying Amara by sending Dean back to 1943 to recover the Hand of God from a doomed submarine. They're unaware that Castiel--secretly Lucifer--is the one who must send Dean back through time and return him.

name: Beyond the Mat
summary: The brothers go to a wake to pay their respects to a dead wrestler who was John's favorite, and discover that the show has left a trail of bodies behind it. Meanwhile, Crowley escapes from Hell and goes to get a weapon capable of stopping Lucifer.

name: Safe House
summary: Sam and Dean take a break from looking for Amara to check out a case of a girl going into a coma. They soon discover that their case is connected to a similar case that Bobby and Rufus investigated several years ago... and never completely solved.

name: Red Meat
summary: Sam and Dean save a couple from two werewolves, but Sam is shot in the process. Dean tries to get Sam and the couple to safety, but Sam dies... and Dean is forced to abandon him.

name: Hell's Angel
summary: Sam and Dean try to convince Crowley to turn over the Horn of Joshua before destroying Lucifer--and Castiel--rather than after they use the Horn to defeat Amara. Meanwhile, an unexpected ally helps Amara heal from her injuries, and Lucifer makes the angels in Heaven an offer they can't refuse.

name: The Chitters
summary: The Winchesters investigate a series of mysterious disappearances every 27 years, and run into a pair of hunters where one is looking for revenge against the creatures that took his brother.

name: Don't Call Me Shurley
summary: The brothers investigate a murder-suicide in Colorado that may be tied to Amara. Meanwhile, Metatron receives a request to edit a new book.

name: All in the Family
summary: Sam and Dean try to come up with a way to rescue Lucifer and discover Chuck's plan to deal with Amara. Meanwhile, a new Prophet is awakened, but he's less than thrilled at the promotion.

name: We Happy Few
summary: To defeat Amara, Sam and Dean will first have to help Chuck and Lucifer reconcile. Once they do, they then must gather the forces of Heaven, Hell, and Magic to weaken Amara so that Chuck can defeat her. However, everything doesn't go quite according to plan.

name: Alpha and Omega
summary: It's the end of the world as Chuck's death extinguishes the sun. Desperate, the Winchesters, Castiel, Crowley, and Rowena come up with a plan... but to succeed, one of them will have to die.

name: Keep Calm and Carry On
summary: While Dean brings Mary up to speed on what has happened in the 30 years since she's died, 'Sam faces torture at the hands of the Men of Letters Meanwhile, Crowley tries to track down a weakened Lucifer, who is hopping from body to body.

name: Mamma Mia
summary: Dean and Castiel continue their efforts to find Sam, and Mary insists on accompanying them. Meanwhile, Crowley recruits Rowena in his attempts to send Lucifer back to the cage.

name: The Foundry
summary: An increasingly nervous Mary suggests to her sons that they investigate two mysterious deaths where the victims were attracted by the call of a baby. Meanwhile, Lucifer forces Rowena to help him preserve Vince's body, while Castiel and Crowley join forces to track him down.

name: American Nightmare
summary: When a priest reports that demons flayed a woman in his church, Sam and Dean investigate and find a religious family at the heart of the problem.

name: The One You've Been Waiting For
summary: The Winchesters stumble upon a Thule plan to steal a pocket watch and abduct a young woman... and discover that Hitler is planning on making a comeback.

name: Celebrating the Life of Asa Fox
summary: Sam and Dean go with Jody to the wake of a legendary Hunter, and discover that there are a few legends about themselves. They also find a killer among them when one of the Hunters turns up dead.

name: Rock Never Dies
summary: Lucifer in Vince Vincente's body stages a reunion tour of Vince's old band Ladyheart. When the Winchesters, Castiel, and Crowley learn of his plan, they head to LA to stop him.

name: LOTUS
summary: Lucifer takes a new host body: the President of the United States. The Winchesters are forced to turn to the British Men of Letters for help to remove Lucifer's essence from his new host, but the Secret Service has other ideas.

name: First Blood
summary: After weeks of imprisonment, Sam and Dean figure out a way to escape the black site prison where they're locked up. Meanwhile, Castiel and Samantha try to get along without them.

name: Lily Sunder Has Some Regrets
summary: When Castiel's former angelic squadmates turn up dead, he goes to investigate and the Winchesters insist on tagging along. They soon discover that the killer has a grudge against angels... and one in particular.

name: Regarding Dean
summary: Sam is forced to call in Rowena when a witch hits Dean with a spell that causes him to lose his memory... and if the spell continues, Dean will soon die when he forgets how to breathe.

name: Stuck in the Middle (With You)
summary: Mary convinces a Hunter, Wally, to call in Sam, Dean, and Castiel to deal with a demon. However, she soon discovers that the intel the Men of Letters gave her is bad... and they face a new, powerful threat.

name: Family Feud
summary: When three teachers are brutally killed, Sam and Dean discover that they were all tied to a salvaged ship that Crowley's son Gavin was going to take to America until Crowley teleported him through time.

name: The Raid
summary: Mary brings Sam to a Men of Letters compound to convince him to join their cause. Meanwhile, Fetch approaches Dean and takes a different approach to recruitment.

name: Somewhere Between Heaven and Hell
summary: Two campers are attacked by a hellhound, and Crowley reveals to the Winchesters that the creature is the First Hellhound. Meanwhile, Lucifer negotiates his release from Crowley's imprisonment, and an angel approaches Castiel with an offer.

name: Ladies Drink Free
summary: Mick convinces Sam and Dean to take him on a case involving a werewolf attack. However, they soon discover that the British Man of Letters has an ulterior motive.

name: The British Invasion
summary: Sam and Dean get a lead on Kelly, but Dagon takes steps to prevent her from making contact with the Winchesters. Meanwhile, Lucifer tries to find a way to deactivate Crowley's wards on his host body, and Castiel is MIA.

name: The Memory Remains
summary: The Men of Letters send Sam and Dean to investigate the case of a murderous goat man in Wisconsin while they check out the bunker to learn all of the Winchesters' secrets.

name: The Future
summary: Castiel fails to kill Kelly yet again, and she tries to convince him that the baby should be born after all. Meanwhile, Sam and Dean discover that Castiel has betrayed them.

name: Twigs & Twine & Tasha Banes
summary: Sam and Dean get a call on one of Mary's phones from Alicia Banes. Alicia and Max are looking for their mother Tasha, and the trail leads to a boarding house in Wyoming. Meanwhile, Mary discovers that Ketch has been lying to her.

name: There's Something About Mary
summary: When Eileen turns up dead, torn apart by a hellhound, Sam and Dean realize that someone is killing the American Hunters. Meanwhile, Mary asks Ketch for a favor.

name: Who We Are
summary: Sam and Dean try to escape the bunker after Ketch turns it into a deathtrap. Meanwhile, the brainwashed Mary goes after Jody and Alex, and Hess puts Phase Two of the Brit's plan into action.

name: All Along the Watchtower
summary: As Kelly prepares to give birth to Lucifer's son Jack, the Winchesters team up with two unexpected allies to stop Lucifer.

name: Lost and Found
summary: Lucifer's son Jack escapes and goes out into the world, and Sam and Dean put things on hold to track him down.

name: The Rising Son
summary: Donatello, the newest Prophet of God, senses God's power and comes looking for him. Meanwhile, a Lord of Hell decides to use Jack to unleash the foulest beasts of Hell. In the other universe, Lucifer and Mary meet the angels including the one who killed "his" Lucifer.

name: Patience
summary: After a wraith kills a psychic, Missouri investigates the death of her friend and calls in Dean and Jody. They help track down Missouri's granddaughter, who also has "the gift" and is the wraith's next target. Meanwhile, Sam tries to help Jack develop his powers.

name: The Big Empty
summary: Two people turn up dead, apparently killed by their deceased love ones. Sam convinces Dean to take Jack with them on the case, and they discover that both victims were seeing a grief counsellor, Mia Vallens. Meanwhile, Castiel meets the keeper of the void that he's trapped in.

name: Advanced Thanatology
summary: Sam suggests that he and Dean work the case of a missing boy by themselves. Dean soon realizes that Sam is deliberately trying to be kind to him, while the Winchesters work a case of a deadly ghost and a house full of trapped spirits.

name: Tombstone
summary: After the Winchesters find Castiel, they reunite him with Jack. Together, the group goes to Tombstone to check out a case of grave robbing, and Jack makes a serious mistake.

name: War of the Worlds
summary: While Lucifer escapes from Michael and proposes an alliance with Castiel, Sam and Dean discover that someone is killing witches and find a familiar face is responsible.

name: The Scorpion and the Frog
summary: To obtain a tracking spell that can locate Jack, Sam and Dean make a deal with the new king of crossroad demons. If the brothers steal a trunk for the new demon, Barthamus, then he'll give them the spell. However, things don't go quite as planned.

name: The Bad Place
summary: An artist turns up dead, his eyes burned out, and the Winchesters suspect that Jack was responsible. However, they soon discover that Jack is trying to help them by finding a dreamwalker so that he can locate Mary for the brothers.

name: Wayward Sisters
summary: When Sam and Dean go missing, Jody calls in Claire. The two of them, along with Patience, Alex, Kaia, and Donna, set out to find the Winchesters in the Bad Place and free them before the portal closes. However, creatures that have come through the portal have other ideas.

name: Breakdown
summary: Donna's niece Wendy goes missing near a truck stop, and she calls on the Winchesters for help. They soon discover that Wendy's abductor is part of an online business providing food to monsters.

name: Various & Sundry Villains
summary: Two young witches use a love spell to get what they want... and they want the Black Grimoire stored at the bunker. Meanwhile, Lucifer and Castiel try to escape from Asmodeus' imprisonment, and are forced to work together.

name: Devil's Bargain
summary: After Castiel makes his way back to Sam and Dean, they set out to find Lucifer and gain an unexpected ally. Meanwhile, Lucifer finds a cooperative angel and makes Heaven's angels an offer that they can't refuse.

name: Good Intentions
summary: Donatello translates the spell and Dean and Castiel go to get the ingredients. Meanwhile, Mary and Jack escape Michael's captivity and meet an old friend for the first time.

name: A Most Holy Man
summary: San and Dean go looking on the black market for the blood of "a most holy man", and become involved trying to recover the stolen skull of St. Peter.

name: Scoobynatural
summary: After fighting a stuffed dinosaur, Sam and Dean are transported into a Scooby cartoon and soon realize that it's haunted.

name: The Thing
summary: Sam and Dean get a lead on the last item they need to open the rift: the Seal of Solomon, at a Men of Letters chapterhouse in Rhode Island. They soon discover something else: a woman imprisoned there for over 80 years. Meanwhile, Asmodeus teaches Ketch his place in the demon prince's hierarchy.

name: Bring 'em Back Alive
summary: Dean and Ketch arrive in the apocalypse world, and Dean sees a familiar face. Meanwhile, Sam and Castiel try to reach Gabriel, while Lucifer grows bored in Heaven.

name: Funeralia
summary: While Castiel goes to Heaven to try and recruit help, Sam and Dean learn that Rowena is killing people in Portland... and Death has an interest in stopping her.

name: Unfinished Business
summary: Sam and Dean track Gabriel to Central City, Colorado, and find him on a trail of vengeance against the god and his sons who he claims betrayed him. Meanwhile, Jack is ready to take on Michael but Mary preaches caution.

name: Beat the Devil
summary: When the group discovers that Gabriel's grace isn't sufficient to open the rift, they turn to another source: Lucifer. However, not all of them survive the trip to Jack and Mary's base.

name: Exodus
summary: On Apocalypse World, Lucifer tries to bond with his son. Meanwhile, the Winchesters come up with a plan to get the resistance fighters to safety, but first they have to rescue Charlie and Ketch.

name: Let the Good Times Roll
summary: Lucifer comes to take Jack on a tour of the universe, but all is not as it seems. Meanwhile, one of the refugees is murdered and the Winchesters try to find the killer.

name: Stranger in a Strange Land
summary: As they search for the missing Dean, Sam and his new band of Hunters--Mary, the Apocalypse World Bobby and Maggie, and Jack--take on a demon who wants to use a hostage Castiel as a bargaining chip to have Sam help him become King of Hell. Meanwhile, Michael travels the world looking for someone who he can work with

name: Gods and Monsters
summary: While Sam, Mary, and Bobby follow a lead in Duluth, Nick and Jack pay visits to people from their pasts.

name: The Scar
summary: Dean discovers that he has a scar on his arm similar to the blade that was used to kill Kaia, and he and Sam set off to Sioux Falls to team up with Jody and find out who has a weapon capable of hurting Michael. Meanwhile, Castiel tries to restore a hexed young girl with Jack's help.

name: Mint Condition
summary: To get Dean out of his funk, Sam takes him along to investigate a case of an action figure coming to life and attacking a comic book store employee.

name: Nightmare Logic
summary: After Maggie disappears while checking out a ghoul sighting, Sam and Dean go to rescue her. They meet up with Mary and Bobby, and run into a number of bizarre manifestations.

name: Optimism
summary: Sam and Charlie team up to get to the bottom of a string of random disappearances; Jack believes that he has found a case and convinces Dean to partner with him on the hunt.

name: Unhuman Nature
summary: When Jack's condition worsens, Sam calls in Rowena and Castiel finds a shaman who might be able to heal their friend. While Dean takes Jack out to experience life, Nick tracks down the person who killed his wife and child.

name: Byzantium
summary: When Jack passes away, Sam, Dean, and Castiel try to find a way to bring him back. Their plan requires the help of an unexpected ally and Castiel traveling to Heaven... where the angel discovers his former home under attack.

name: The Spear
summary: Michael prepares to unleash his army on an unsuspecting city on Christmas Eve, and only Sam, Dean, Castiel, and Jack can stop him.

name: Nihilism
summary: Sam, Castiel, and Jack manage to capture Michael, and seek out a way to free Dean from the archangel's possession... while Michael's monsters move in on them.

name: Damaged Goods
summary: Dean makes a decision based on the information he was given, and then pays a visit to Mary. Meanwhile, Nick tracks down the demon that killed his family.

name: Prophet and Loss
summary: Sam and Dean go on one last case on their way to trap Dean at the bottom of the ocean, and discover a prophet who is killing people even though Donatello is still in a coma and hasn't died yet.

name: Lebanon
summary: Sam and Dean find a magical pearl that grants the user's "heart's desire". However, what Dean gets when he makes his wish isn't what he expects.

name: Ouroboros
summary: The hunt for a new monster goes awry when Dean is knocked unconscious, releasing Michael from his imprisonment. The archangel seeks out a new host body, and only one person can stop him.

name: Peace of Mind
summary: While Sam and Castiel investigate a small Arkansas town where a teenager's head exploded, Dean takes Jack to see Donatello so they can find out what being without a soul feels like.

name: Don't Go in the Woods
summary: While Sam and Dean go on a monster hunt against a monster that they can find out little about, Jack makes new friends with the local Lebanon teenagers but things go horribly wrong.

name: Game Night
summary: Mary and Dean go to investigate when Donatello calls with a plea for help. Jack meets with his father's vessel, and Castiel teams up with Anael to find a way to contact God.

name: Absence
summary: Sam and Dean race to discover what happened to Mary, while Castiel checks in Heaven to discover if her soul is there. Meanwhile, Jack turns to Rowena to help him cope with the enormity of what he's done.

name: Jack in the Box
summary: Duma approaches Jack and offers him a chance to earn redemption. Afterward, the Winchesters and Castiel learn of a series of Biblical attacks and the brothers figure out the one to stop Jack... they hope.

name: Moriah
summary: Chuck appears to provide a solution to the Jack problem, but his help is less than helpful.

name: Back and to the Future
summary: The Winchesters and Castiel gain an unexpected ally as the souls released from Hell by Chuck threaten to overwhelm them. Their ally soon tells them the magnitude of the threat that now faces them.

name: Raising Hell
summary: Rowena arrives in Harlan to help Castiel and the Winchesters contain the ghosts. Two unexpected allies appear to help them, but things don't go as planned. Meanwhile, Chuck holds a family reunion in Reno.

name: The Rupture
summary: To seal the rupture, Castiel and Belphegor must travel to Hell to find a relic with the power to summon the spirits back. Rowena asks Sam to help her, and Ketch gets a visitor.

name: Atomic Monsters
summary: The Winchesters travel to Iowa to investigate a vampire-related death, and soon find themselves in the middle of a family affair.

name: Proverbs 17:3
summary: Sam continues to have dreams of killing Dean, and he and Dean investigate a case in Colorado where five victims have had their heart torn out.

name: Golden Time
summary: Sam and Dean meet an old friend, and Sam goes to Rowena's apartment to find a resurrection spell. Meanwhile, Castiel finds himself drawn into a monster-hunting case when a local boy turns up dead.

name: Last Call
summary: Dean goes on a Hunt by himself and meets an old friend. Castiel returns to the bunker and calls in a specialist when Sam's condition takes a turn for the worse.

name: Our Father, Who Aren't in Heaven
summary: Sam, Dean, and Castiel travel to Hell to talk to Michael and see if he knows Chuck's weakness, and they meet the new ruler of Hell. When they return to Earth, the Winchesters are reunited with a member of the family they thought was gone for good.

name: The Trap
summary: Sam and Eileen are faced with the brutal truth. Meanwhile Dean and Cass work together in the hopes of getting a step ahead of Chuck.

name: The Heroes' Journey
summary: Sam and Dean hit the road to help an old friend, but it appears that their luck may have finally run out and they are the ones who may be in need of rescue.

name: The Gamblers
summary: Sam and Dean press their luck in a winner-takes-all game of pool. Meanwhile, Castiel hunts down a would-be murderer, but not for reasons one might think.

name: Galaxy Brain
summary: Sam and Dean respond to a frantic call and together along with Castiel, Jack and Jody, assist in an extraordinary and heartbreaking rescue. Billie surprises everyone with a visit to the bunker.

name: Destiny's Child
summary: A search for the one thing that may give the Winchesters an edge against God leads Sam and Dean to Jo's door and to a secret that may have died with Ruby. Meanwhile, Castiel asks Jack to do the unthinkable to help the brothers in their quest.

name: Last Holiday
summary: Sam and Dean discover a wood nymph living in the bunker who is determined to protect her family, at any cost.

name: Gimme Shelter
summary: Castiel and Jack work a case involving members of a local church. Meanwhile, Sam and Dean go off in search of Amara.

name: Drag Me Away (From You)
summary: Sam and Dean are asked to investigate the murder of a childhood friend, calling them back to a motel from their past and perplexing the brothers with a case they thought was solved a long time ago.

name: Unity
summary: Dean hits the road with Jack who needs to complete a final ritual in the quest to beat Chuck. A difference of opinion leaves Sam and Castiel behind looking for answers to questions of their own.

name: Despair
summary: With the plan in full motion, Sam, Dean, Castiel and Jack fight for the good of the common goal.

name: Inherit the Earth
summary: Everything is on the line as the battle against God continues. A familiar face returns to join the fight.

name: Carry On
summary: After 15 seasons, the longest running sci fi series in the US is coming to an end. Baby, it's the final ride for saving people and hunting things.
